  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2080 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/asparagus-mushroom-truffle-pizzas-62324442b6f6fa03f608246e
servings: 2
cuisine: Italian
time required: 35 minutes
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to bottom position (bottom and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @Cremini Mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).
Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}; cut crosswise on a diagonal
into 1 1/2-inch-thick pieces and place in a #medium bowl{} (large bowl for 4). Toss with a
drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Halve @Red Grapes{2.25%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook,
stirring occasionally, until golden and softened, ~{3-5%minutes} (they'll finish cooking
in step 4). Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat.

While mushrooms cook, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Cheese Roux Concentrate{1%ounce},
@Cream Cheese{2%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Microwave for ~{30%seconds},
then stir in as much @Truffle Zest{2%g} as you like (we used it all!) until smooth and combined.

Open @Thin Crust Pizza Dough{7%ounce}; separate sheets at dotted line. (TIP: Use a knife to
separate cleanly.) Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} (2 sheets for 4); gently stretch
each dough sheet into a 6-by-9-inch rectangle. Spread with truffle sauce, leaving a ½-inch
space around the edges. Top with half the @Mozzarella Cheese{1%cup}. Add mushrooms and
asparagus in a layer; top with remaining mozzarella.

Bake on bottom rack until crust is crispy, cheese melts, and veggies are tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.
(For 4, bake on bottom and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.)

While pizzas bake, wash out pan used for mushrooms. Heat pan over medium-high heat. Add
@Almonds{½%ounce}; cook, stirring, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan
from heat.

Transfer toasted almonds to a #plate{}. Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{8%teaspoon} in same pan
over medium-high heat. Add @Prosciutto{10%ounce} in a single layer (for 4 servings, cook
in batches if necessary); sear until browned and crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> TIP: For even crisping, use a spatula to press down on prosciutto. If it begins to brown
> too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Wash out #bowl{} used for truffle sauce. In bowl, combine half the @White Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(all for 4 servings), @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of @Sugar{}.
Season with salt and pepper.

Wash out bowl used for asparagus. In bowl, toss @Arugula{2%ounce} and grapes with as much
dressing as you like. Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle salad with almonds.

Quarter pizzas; halve quarters on a diagonal to create eight small slices per pizza.

Halve @Burrata{4%ounce} and divide between pizzas. Top burrata with a drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper. Divide pizzas and salad between plates. Serve.

Break prosciutto into bite-size pieces; sprinkle over pizzas.